1. Create a Scheduler object: This is the core engine that determines scheduling behavior, due dates, stability updates, etc.
2. Create a Card object and add it to the database: When a user creates a new card, you instantiate a Card, which starts in the Learning state. (can postgres save card as a python dict?)
3. User studies the card and selects a rating: user gives a rating from the frontend like easy, good, hard or again. (but, how do i determine which card to display? there will be many cards to review right?)
4. Pass the card, rating, and timestamp to the scheduler: The scheduler will update:
    card.state: Learning, Review, or Relearning
    card.step: Current step in learning/relearning
    card.stability and card.difficulty: Memory model parameters
    card.due: ğŸ“… next due time
    card.last_review: â° When the review happened
5. Store the updated card (and optionally review log) back to the DB

